The paper proposes two methods for detecting and mapping informal settlements using satellite imagery, which involves computer vision and image processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geographic information systems (GIS) and remote sensing, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
